        <instrument_desc>
 
 
  Instrument Overview
  ===================
    The CTIO 1.5-meter Cassegrain spectrograph is an ultraviolet
    transmitting grating spectrograph which is used at the f/7.5 focus
    where the scale is 18.1 arcseconds/mm. It is identical to the 2.1-meter
    telescope White Cassegrain spectrograph at Kitt Peak National
    Observatory and therefore allows one to obtain similar spectrograms in
    both hemispheres.
 
    Plate Scale (at f/7.5 focal plane)      18.06 arcsec/mm
    Slit Length                             25.4 mm, 459.7 arcsec
    Collimator Focal Length                 766.1 mm
    Point source collimated beam diameter   101.6 mm
    Collimator-to-Camera Angle              55 degrees
    Grating size                            127 152 mm
    Camera Focal Length                     160 mm
    Demagnification                         4.788
    Plate Scale (at detector)               86.7 arcsec/mm

